CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 4, 1966, pg. 4B reads: "50th Anniversary - Denorah Grand Chapter, Order of Eastern Star, celebrated its 50th Anniversary at a banquet May 20, at Taylor's Restaurant on Route 30. Among the distinguished guests was Mrs. Pattee Miller of Reading, Grand Matron of the chapter. (Harris Photo)"
TitMainTitle: Member of the Denorah Grand Chapter, Order of Eastern Star, wearing floor length light colored gown posing in front of folk style landscape mural, in Taylor's Restaurant for fiftieth anniversary banquet, Westmoreland County
